            <thetext>Some simple actions need the class list without any kind of variants (e.g. 
copy-files, fix, ...), while the compile actions need the variant settings. So 
far, in a compile job the class list has been computed twice, without any 
variants (for simple actions), and with variants (for the compile action). If 
the variant computation is done early enough, both class list computations can 
be done using real variants (including the empty variant set if none is given). 
This avoids costly re-computation of the class list for the compile action.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
